            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-21 11:53:41" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the bony framework of the head, especially the upper portion</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>skull (in the NT κρανίον is used only as a name for the hill of Golgotha).</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In rendering κρανίου τόπος ‘place of the skull’ it may be necessary to indicate clearly the relationship between place and skull. A literal rendering of such a phrase might simply mean ‘a place where there was a skull.’ However the meaning of Golgotha has been interpreted generally as ‘a hill resembling a skull’ and therefore κρανίου τόπος may be more satisfactorily rendered as ‘a place resembling a skull’ or ‘a hill looking like a skull.’ See {D:93.453}.</Comments>
